    Interface Description
    GameInterface
    This interface provides the game with the following methods.
    Intelligence
    An interface for the AI.

    This interface is for the figureMovements.

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bishop
    The bishop-figures of the game.
    BishopMovement
    The bishop's move set.
    Blitz
    This class contains the Blitz-chess rules.
    Board
    The board contains the 64 tiles of the board.
    Cemetery
    Whenever a figure is beaten it is put on the cemetery.
    Computer
    This class present an AI-player as as second player.
    Figure
    The Figure class is the abstract parent class for our different figures.
    Game
    In this class the game is running.
    Human
    In this Class human players are created.
    King
    The king-figures of the game.
    KingMovement
    The king's move set.

    The knight-figures of the game.
    KnightMovement
    The knight's move set.
    Normal
    This class contains the normal rules for chess
    Pawn
    The pawn-figures of the game.
    PawnMovement
    The pawn's move set.
    Player
    The super-class for player creation, human as well as AI.
    Position
    The position of the figures.
    Queen
    The queen-figures of the game.
    Rook
    The rook-figures of the game.
    RookMovement
    The rook's move set.
    Tile
    A tile on the board which can contain a figure or hold an empty space.
    Timer
    This class provides the timers for the mode Blitz chess.
